     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiOccupation[in, {k1, k2, ...}] returns a list of the expectation \
values of occupation on fermion modes in {k1, k2, ...} with respect to \
BravyiState in. BravyiOccupation[in] is equivalent to BravyiOccupation[in, \
Range[n]], where n is the number of fermion modes for which input Bravyi or \
BdG state in is defined for. BravyiOccupation[data] or BravyiOccupation[data, \
{k1, k2, ...}] shows a dynamic progress indicator while calculating the \
occupation for an (typically large) array data of Bravyi or BdG states. \
BravyiOccupation[{k1, k2, ...}] represents an operator form of \
BravyiOccupation to be applied to Bravyi or BdG state.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "BravyiOccupation", "titlemodifier" -> "", 
